    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-11-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751.8215/177½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to">King</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: The receipt is acknowledged of
                    your letter of November 8, 1921, relative to the Franco-Liberian Boundary
                    delimitation.</p>
                <p>In reply I beg to say that the Department will be glad to use its good offices
                    with the French Government as requested to secure that Government’s consent to
                    the resumption and completion of the delimitation of the boundary as soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <p>The matter of designating for appointment by the Liberian Government a qualified
                    man to assist Commissioner Daves with the Boundary survey will receive
                    attention.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fred Morris Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
